@NODE INTRO "Introduction"

                         Introduction

@{b}@{fg shine}THIS PROGRAM WILL ONLY PRODUCE RANDOM NUMBERS.@{ub}@{fg filltext}


The Lottery2002 (OS3.5/9) V2.1 is freeware.

It uses the new boopsi classes in OS3.5/9, & was compilied using StormC 3 Pro.

I have included my 'C' source code (it my not look pretty but it works for me).

Lottery2002 Very simply generates 2 sets of random numbers for the Wedensday &
Saturday's National Lottery in GB.


If by any chance you win the Lottery please remember what COMPUTER choose the numbers.


GOOD LUCK.  

@ENDNODE

@NODE REQUIRE "Requirements"

Lottery2002 requires:

- OS 3.5/9  & 68020/30/40/60


@{b}@{fg fill}- Optional for speaking the choosen numbers.@{ub}@{fg filltext}
- Translator.library =>v36. in LIBS:
- Narrator.device. in DEVS:
@{b}- Both of these were copied from my old A600.@{ub}

- this the mount list to mount the speak device

/* Speak-Handler mount entry*/

Handler         = L:Speak-Handler
Stacksize       = 6000
Priority        = 5
GlobVec         = -1

Save it as a text file, add a Project icon with a
Default tool c:Mount and a tool type ACTIVATE=0

Put them both in DEVS/DOSDrivers


 tested with:
            - A1200 + 130Mb ram + Blizzard 1260 Accelerator + SCSI interface.


@ENDNODE

@NODE USAGE "Usage"

                         Usage

Lottery2002 V2.1 can be run from a CLI or from Workbench.
There are no commands or ToolTypes required.

There are 3 buttons at the bottom of the Lottery2002 window.

- @{b}Start@{ub} @{i}(key S) @{ui} Starts to generate random numbers for Wedensday & Saturday.
- @{b}Speak@{ub} @{i}(key E) @{ui} Speaks the choosen numbers, if disabled could not find the
                 @{b}Translator.library@{ub} or the @{b}Narrator.device@{ub}.
- @{b}Quit@{ub}  @{i}(key Q) @{ui} Quits Lottery2002.

The Lottery2002 window also has a Iconify gadget and Menus attached to it. The
menus do the same as the buttons & has an About... item.

NOTE: if you rename Lottery2002 it won't use it's icon as I have hard coded the icon
name as Lottery2002.

Gadget help is shown in the Workbench screen tile bar.

@ENDNODE

